  "contents": [
    {
      "id": "b1-u2-l1-c1",
      "lessonId": "b1-u2-l1",
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Lesson Introduction",
      "order": 1,
      "content": {
        "textEn": "In this lesson, you will learn the 13 Mongolian vowels, their classification, vowel harmony, and basic pronunciation patterns through repetition drills and vocabulary practice."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "b1-u2-l1-c2",
      "lessonId": "b1-u2-l1",
      "type": "classification",
      "title": "Classification of Vowels",
      "order": 2,
      "content": {
        "summary": "Mongolian has 13 vowel letters. Seven are basic vowels and six are auxiliary vowels.",
        "groups": [
          {
            "title": "Basic vowels (7)",
            "items": ["а", "э", "и", "о", "у", "ө", "ү"]
          },
          {
            "title": "Auxiliary vowels (6)",
            "items": ["е", "ё", "й", "ы", "ю", "я"]
          },
          {
            "title": "Masculine vowels",
            "items": ["а", "о", "у", "ы", "я", "ё", "ю"]
          },
          {
            "title": "Feminine vowels",
            "items": ["э", "ө", "ү", "е", "и", "ю"]
          },
          {
            "title": "Neuter vowels",
            "items": ["и", "й"]
          },
          {
            "title": "Rounded vowels",
            "items": ["о", "у", "ө", "ү"]
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "b1-u2-l1-c3",
      "lessonId": "b1-u2-l1",
      "type": "grammar_note",
      "title": "Grammar Notes",
      "order": 3,
      "content": {
        "notes": [
          "Mongolian has 13 vowel letters, including 7 basic vowels and 6 auxiliary vowels.",
          "The grapheme ы is not pronounced like the Russian ы.",
          "The 13 vowel sounds are grouped into masculine vowels, feminine vowels, and neutral vowels.",
          "In one word, vowels of one series usually appear together. This is called vowel harmony.",
          "Words with masculine vowels are called masculine words.",
          "Words with feminine vowels are called feminine words.",
          "The vowel и is neutral and may appear in both types of words.",
          "The vowels о, у, ө, ү are rounded vowels.",
          "Ү is pronounced as a short rounded sound similar to a short English u-type sound.",
          "О is an open rounded vowel.",
          "Ө is a rounded central vowel.",
          "Э is a close vowel and may sometimes sound like i in some feminine words.",
          "The letter е may represent [je] or [jö], and sometimes [j].",
          "The letter ё may represent [jo], and in final position may sound like [j].",
          "The letter ю may represent [ju] or [jü]."
        ]
      }
    },
